Key Match Events: Giannis Antetokounmpo had 41 points and 14 rebounds.
Paolo Banchero scored 34 points in his return from injury.
Damian Lillard added 29 points for the Bucks, including crucial free throws with 9.3 seconds left.
Cole Anthony had 18 points and seven rebounds for Orlando.
Tristan da Silva had 16 points and 10 rebounds for Orlando.
Bobby Portis scored 11 points and grabbed seven rebounds off the bench for Milwaukee.
The Bucks moved into a virtual tie with the Magic for fourth place in the East with their third straight win.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Magic challenged a foul call on Anthony Black with 9.3 seconds left, but it was upheld.
The Bucks shot 52% to offset nine missed free throws.
